---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Building Your Own MCP Server: Starting from a Class-Notes Helper — AI Agent Puzzle"
  description="Your first MCP server isn't about building a bigger system. It's about building a clearer, safer, more situation-fit set of tools. Start with a tiny server that only handles class notes: list them, read them, and produce a reflection draft — with sharp boundaries."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container ai-agent-custom-server">
      <a class="back-link" href="/">&larr; Back to Home</a>

      <header class="detail-header">
        <h1 class="detail-title">Building Your Own MCP Server: Starting from a Class-Notes Helper</h1>
        <p class="detail-subtitle">
          We've already used off-the-shelf MCPs and seen how Notion can search, read, and create pages for us. But off-the-shelf MCPs usually pack a lot of capability — great for general use, not always great for beginners. Often, what we really want is for AI to <strong>finish one small, clearly-scoped task</strong>.
        </p>
      </header>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        So what we're going to build next isn't a big, full, do-everything AI system. We're just going to build a tiny MCP server: it can read class notes from a specific folder and produce a reflection draft in a fixed format, <strong>without messing with the original notes</strong>.
      </p>

      <div class="highlight-card">
        <p class="highlight-text">
          Building your own MCP server isn't about building something bigger.<br/>
          It's about building <strong>a clearer, safer, more situation-fit tool surface</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: MCP Server as tool provider -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Think of an MCP Server as a "Tool Provider"</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        The first time people hear "make your own MCP server," they often think they have to build a whole new AI. They don't. The AI is still Gemini. The MCP server we're building is more like <strong>a "tool provider" standing on the side</strong>.
      </p>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">It tells Gemini CLI:</p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li><strong>Which tools</strong> are available here</li>
        <li><strong>What each tool does</strong></li>
        <li><strong>What inputs</strong> each tool needs</li>
        <li><strong>What it returns</strong> after running</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        The MCP Python SDK lets you build a server that exposes <code>tools</code>, <code>resources</code>, and <code>prompts</code>; Gemini CLI can connect to those servers via <code>settings.json</code> and let the model call into them.
      </p>

      <div class="callout-card">
        <p class="callout-text">
          So picture it like this: <strong>Gemini CLI is where you and the AI work together; the MCP server is a small set of tools you've built yourself.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: stdio vs HTTP -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">This Time We're Using stdio, Not HTTP</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        When we connected to Notion's MCP earlier, we used HTTP — Gemini CLI dialed into a URL that already existed. This time is different. We're building a <strong>local MCP server</strong>, and we're using stdio.
      </p>

      <div class="highlight-card">
        <p class="highlight-text">
          You can think of stdio simply as:<br/>
          <strong>Gemini CLI launches a Python program on your machine, and talks to it through standard input and standard output.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        So this time there's no URL like <code>https://mcp.notion.com/mcp</code>, and we're not using <code>--transport http</code> to dial a remote service. The shape of it is more like this:
      </p>

      <div class="flow-card">
        <div class="flow-step">Gemini CLI</div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">↓ launches</div>
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--accent">python server.py</div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">↓ provides</div>
        <div class="flow-step">tools / resources / prompts</div>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Gemini CLI supports several MCP transports. stdio means "spawn a subprocess and talk over stdin/stdout"; the HTTP-style transports dial an HTTP or SSE endpoint instead.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: What we are building -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">What We're Building This Time</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Let's not touch the Notion API yet. Building your first MCP server while juggling Python, MCP, an API, keys, permissions, and network requests at the same time makes it <strong>really hard to tell where things go wrong</strong>.
      </p>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        So for the first version, we're building something very small:
      </p>

      <div class="project-card">
        <p class="project-label">YOUR FIRST CUSTOM MCP SERVER</p>
        <p class="project-name">Class-Notes Helper</p>
        <p class="project-desc">
          It only handles Markdown notes inside a specific folder on your machine.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="boundary-grid">
        <div class="boundary-col boundary-col--can">
          <p class="boundary-label">What it can do</p>
          <ul class="check-list boundary-list">
            <li>List <strong>which class notes</strong> exist</li>
            <li>Read the contents of <strong>one specific note</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Create a new reflection draft</strong> based on a note</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="boundary-col boundary-col--cant">
          <p class="boundary-label">What it can't do</p>
          <ul class="cross-list boundary-list">
            <li>Cannot <strong>delete</strong> the original notes</li>
            <li>Cannot <strong>modify</strong> the original notes</li>
            <li>Cannot read files <strong>outside the designated folder</strong></li>
            <li>Cannot auto-<strong>submit</strong> assignments or publish content</li>
            <li>Cannot produce the student's <strong>final version</strong> for them</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="callout-card">
        <p class="callout-text">
          This design looks small, but that smallness matters. A good AI workflow isn't judged by how much it can do up front — it's judged by whether it can <strong>do one small thing reliably, inside clear boundaries</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Tool surface design first -->
      <h2 class="detail-heading">Design the Tool Surface First — Don't Rush to Code</h2>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        Before writing any code, let's think the tool surface through. The class-notes helper breaks down into <strong>three kinds of things</strong>:
      </p>

      <!-- Tools -->
      <div class="case-header">
        <p class="case-label">TOOLS</p>
        <h2 class="case-title">The Things That Actually Do Something</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        We'll build four tools.
      </p>

      <div class="tool-box">
        <p class="tool-box__label">Tool 1</p>
        <p class="tool-box__name"><code>hello</code></p>
        <p class="tool-box__desc">
          A sanity check — confirms the MCP server actually started up.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tool-box">
        <p class="tool-box__label">Tool 2</p>
        <p class="tool-box__name"><code>list_notes</code></p>
        <p class="tool-box__desc">
          Lists which class notes are in the <code>class_notes</code> folder.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tool-box">
        <p class="tool-box__label">Tool 3</p>
        <p class="tool-box__name"><code>read_note</code></p>
        <p class="tool-box__desc">
          Reads one specific class note.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tool-box">
        <p class="tool-box__label">Tool 4</p>
        <p class="tool-box__name"><code>create_reflection_draft</code></p>
        <p class="tool-box__desc">
          Creates a new reflection draft inside the <code>drafts</code> folder.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Resource -->
      <div class="case-header">
        <p class="case-label">RESOURCE</p>
        <h2 class="case-title">Fixed Reference Material for the AI</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        We'll also expose one resource:
      </p>

      <div class="tool-box">
        <p class="tool-box__label">Resource</p>
        <p class="tool-box__name"><code>course://reflection-rules</code></p>
        <p class="tool-box__desc">
          Holds the fixed rules for writing a class reflection draft.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">For example:</p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>A reflection should cover <strong>"what I understood," "where I'm still stuck," and "how I might apply this"</strong></li>
        <li>Don't finish the student's final assignment for them</li>
        <li>If the source material is thin, <strong>flag it to the user</strong> — don't fill in the gaps yourself</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Prompt -->
      <div class="case-header">
        <p class="case-label">PROMPT</p>
        <h2 class="case-title">A Reusable Workflow</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="detail-paragraph">
        We'll also define one prompt:
      </p>

      <div class="tool-box">
        <p class="tool-box__label">Prompt</p>
        <p class="tool-box__name"><code>draft_reflection</code></p>
        <p class="tool-box__desc">
          Wraps "produce a class reflection draft" into a fixed flow.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="detail-paragraph">The flow looks roughly like this:</p>

      <ol class="reflect-list reflect-list--single">
        <li class="reflect-item">
          <span class="reflect-num">1</span>
          <span class="reflect-text">First, <strong>read</strong> the chosen note</span>
        </li>
        <li class="reflect-item">
          <span class="reflect-num">2</span>
          <span class="reflect-text">Then pull out the <strong>points relevant to the topic</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="reflect-item">
          <span class="reflect-num">3</span>
          <span class="reflect-text">Consult the <strong>reflection rules</strong></span>
        </li>
        <li class="reflect-item">
          <span class="reflect-num">4</span>
          <span class="reflect-text">Show the draft to the user for <strong>confirmation</strong> first</span>
        </li>
        <li class="reflect-item">
          <span class="reflect-num">5</span>
          <span class="reflect-text">Only after the user agrees, <strong>create the draft file</strong></span>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="highlight-card">
        <p class="highlight-text">
          Once the tools, resource, and prompt are clear in your head,<br/>
          <strong>the implementation gets a lot easier.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ai-agent-custom-server {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Header */
  .detail-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-title {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .detail-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .detail-subtitle strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Section headings */
  .detail-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .detail-paragraph {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .detail-paragraph strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Case header (TOOLS / RESOURCE / PROMPT) */
  .case-label {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-0);
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-4);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #fff;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .case-title {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 2.4;
  }

  .case-header {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
  }

  /* Inline code */
  :global(.detail-paragraph) code,
  :global(.detail-subtitle) code,
  :global(.check-list) code,
  :global(.cross-list) code,
  :global(.callout-text) code,
  :global(.highlight-text) code,
  :global(.tool-box__desc) code,
  :global(.boundary-list) code,
  :global(.reflect-text) code {
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  /* Check list */
  .check-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .check-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .check-list li::before {
    content: '\2713';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .check-list li strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Cross list (✗ items) */
  .cross-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .cross-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.9;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .cross-list li::before {
    content: '\2717';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .cross-list li strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Callout card */
  .callout-card {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-8);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-8);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .callout-text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .callout-text strong {
    color: var(--color-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Highlight card (key takeaway) */
  .highlight-card {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-8);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
  }

  .highlight-text {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-heading);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .highlight-text strong {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Flow card (Gemini CLI ↓ python server.py ↓ tools) */
  .flow-card {
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .flow-step {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-2);
    background-color: #fff;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
  }

  .flow-step--accent {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .flow-arrow {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Project card (Class-Notes Helper) */
  .project-card {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-8);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .project-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .project-name {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .project-desc {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Boundary grid (can / can't) */
  .boundary-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }

  .boundary-col {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .boundary-col--can {
    border-top: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  .boundary-col--cant {
    border-top: 3px solid var(--color-text-secondary);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .boundary-label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .boundary-list {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .boundary-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Tool box */
  .tool-box {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-6);
    border: 1px dashed var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .tool-box__label {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .tool-box__name {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-heading);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .tool-box__name code {
    padding: 0.15em 0.5em;
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 1em;
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-tag-text);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .tool-box__desc {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* Reflect list (steps in the prompt flow) */
  .reflect-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-6);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .reflect-list--single {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .reflect-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .reflect-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 1.75rem;
    height: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .reflect-text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-heading);
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .reflect-text strong {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .boundary-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .reflect-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .case-title {
      font-size: var(--text-lg);
    }

    .callout-card,
    .highlight-card {
      padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-6);
    }

    .project-card {
      padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-6);
    }

    .tool-box {
      padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    }

    .flow-card {
      padding: var(--space-5) var(--space-4);
    }

    .reflect-item {
      gap: var(--space-3);
      padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    }
  }
</style>
